title: Southern Miss QB Nick Mullens picks up a pair of weekly honors
text:
Southern Miss QB Nick Mullens picks up a pair of weekly honors By PATRICK MAGEE pmagee@sunherald.com Twitter: Patrick_Magee October 5, 2015 2015-10-05T17:53:06Z TIM ISBELL â€” SUN HERALD Buy Photo 
Southern Miss junior quarterback Nick Mullens picked up a pair of honors Monday following his impressive performance in Saturday's 49-14 victory over North Texas. 
Mullens was named the Conference USA Offensive Player of the Week and was also chosen as one of eight Manning Award Stars of the Week. 
Mullens was 27-of-36 passes for 325 yards and four touchdowns. He also ran two times for 21 yards and a score. 
The performance was Mullens' eighth 300-yard passing game of his career. 
Southern Miss sits at 3-2 and 1-0 in Conference USA play as it prepares to travel to Marshall for a 6 p.m. game on Friday. The game will be televised by CBS Sports Network. 
Mullens ranks fifth in the nation in passing yardage with 1,691 yards. He has completed 124-of-188 passes with 14 touchdowns and three interceptions.
